  "notes": "Proto-Berber / Common Berber. Afroasiatic > Berber branch. Reconstructed ancestor of all Tamazight varieties (Kabyle, Tachelhit, Tarifit, Central Atlas, Tuareg, Nafusi, etc.). ~30–40 million speakers across North Africa. KEY SUBSTRATE EFFECTS ON MAGHREBI ARABIC: (1) Emphatic (pharyngealised) consonant reinforcement; (2) Extreme consonant cluster tolerance (→ Moroccan vowel deletion); (3) Minimal vowel system (3 phonemic: /a i u/ + ə); (4) Spirantisation of stops (b→β, t→θ, k→x). Traditional script: Tifinagh (Tuareg preserve oldest forms). Refs: Kossmann (1999), Chaker (1995), Louali & Philippson (2004).",
